### FINDINGS
[F-012-01] Current-state-only discipline is still phase-parent-scoped in live spec-kit: peck says `product.md` “only ever describes what currently exists” before planning stories, while live `PHASE_PARENT_CONTENT` runs only when `is_phase_parent($folder)` is true and skips regular folders. peck: `external/peck-master/README.md:48`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/rules/check-phase-parent-content.sh:19`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/rules/check-phase-parent-content.sh:21`. SHIPPED-ALREADY? partial. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: low-medium. RISK: medium false-positive noise. BLAST-RADIUS: validator + docs.

[F-012-02] 003 intended broader long-lived-doc discipline, but its own shipped-state docs still say planned/not implemented: 003 targets `implementation-summary.md` wave 1 and defers non-parent `spec.md`; its implementation summary says “nothing has shipped yet” and verification is pending. peck: `external/peck-master/README.md:48`; 003: `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/spec.md:94`, `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/spec.md:104`, `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/implementation-summary.md:51`, `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/implementation-summary.md:96`. SHIPPED-ALREADY? no for generalized rule. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: medium. RISK: medium. BLAST-RADIUS: implementation-summary validation across spec folders.

[F-012-03] Non-parent `spec.md` generalization is explicit residue, not an accidental omission: 003 says non-parent `spec.md` is deferred wave 2 to limit false positives, while live rule documentation says `PHASE_PARENT_CONTENT` skips regular spec folders and phase children. peck: `external/peck-master/README.md:46`, `external/peck-master/README.md:48`; 003/spec-kit: `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/spec.md:94`, `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/spec.md:104`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/validation/validation_rules.md:160`. SHIPPED-ALREADY? no. VERDICT: DEFER. EFFORT: medium-high. RISK: high false positives in requirements/history sections. BLAST-RADIUS: all non-parent spec folders.

[F-012-04] Spec-kit lacks a curated product.md analog in the documented spec-folder surface: peck’s template has current shipped features, non-goals, and honest limitations; spec-kit’s documented layout has per-packet `spec.md`, `implementation-summary.md`, `handover.md`, `resource-map.md`, and metadata `description.json`, but no single curated “system is now” narrative surface. peck: `external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/product.md:5`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/product.md:10`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/product.md:14`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md:182`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md:184`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md:190`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md:192`. SHIPPED-ALREADY? no. VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: medium. RISK: medium duplication/drift. BLAST-RADIUS: docs/templates/memory indexing, not runtime.

[F-012-05] `description.json` is metadata, not the peck-style narrative surface: peck’s `product.md` asks for product purpose, shipped features, non-goals, and limitations; 003 `description.json` contains level, spec folder, keywords, timestamp, spec id, folder slug, parent chain, and memory sequence. peck: `external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/product.md:1`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/product.md:5`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/product.md:10`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/templates/product.md:14`; 003: `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/description.json:2`, `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/description.json:3`, `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/description.json:5`, `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/description.json:11`. SHIPPED-ALREADY? no. VERDICT: ADOPT curated narrative separately; keep `description.json` metadata-only. EFFORT: medium. RISK: low-medium. BLAST-RADIUS: new/reference doc + indexing.

### RULED_OUT
- Phase-parent current-state discipline already shipped: live registry has `PHASE_PARENT_CONTENT` at warn severity and points to `check-phase-parent-content.sh`; docs say it scans phase-parent `spec.md` for migration-history tokens. `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/validator-registry.json:115`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/validator-registry.json:118`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/validator-registry.json:120`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md:235`.
- Fence/comment-aware token scanning already shipped for phase parents: the script skips fenced blocks and HTML comments before matching tokens. `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/rules/check-phase-parent-content.sh:33`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/rules/check-phase-parent-content.sh:35`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/rules/check-phase-parent-content.sh:36`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/rules/check-phase-parent-content.sh:43`.
- Hard-blocking current-state enforcement was already rejected by 003: 003 scopes the broadening to INFO/advisory and excludes ERROR severity. `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/spec.md:85`, `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/spec.md:95`, `001-peck-teachings-adoption/003-current-state-discipline/spec.md:101`.

